SIMPLE: undulated
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Undulated
<hw>Un"du*la`ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Resembling, or in the nature of, waves; having a wavy surface;
undulatory.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Waved obtusely up and down, near
the margin, as a leaf or corolla; wavy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Formed with elevations and
depressions resembling waves; having wavelike color markings; <as>as, an
<ex>undulated</ex> shell</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undulating</ent>⟦br⟧
